    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail and dice your<strong> carrot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Heat a very large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped onion</strong> and<strong> diced carrot</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rich-mushroom-ragu-linguine/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> white cup mushrooms</strong> to a<strong> food processor</strong> and pulse for 5 secs or until roughly blitzed</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rich-mushroom-ragu-linguine/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and carrot have softened, add the <strong>blitzed mushrooms</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> dried oregano</strong> to the pan and increase the heat to medium-high</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until the mushrooms are beginning to soften</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and stir in your<strong> soy sauce</strong> and <strong>Marmite</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rich-mushroom-ragu-linguine/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>to the pan with your <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong>,<strong> drained lentils</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 12-15 min or until thickened to a bolognese-like consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>mushroom rag\u00f9</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rich-mushroom-ragu-linguine/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>linguine </strong>and return to the pot, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rich-mushroom-ragu-linguine/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the linguine is cooking, chop your<strong> basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Peel your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> until you end up with a pile of cheese shavings</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rich-mushroom-ragu-linguine/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained linguine</strong> to the mushroom rag\u00f9 and gently stir together until the rag\u00f9 begins to stick to the linguine - this is your <strong>rich</strong> <strong>mushroom rag\u00f9 linguine</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/rich-mushroom-ragu-linguine/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>rich mushroom rag\u00f9 linguine</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> chopped basil</strong>,<strong> Italian hard cheese shavings</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
